// EXPECTED: compile error
//
// Same root cause as async_called_as_regular.zer, but the call site is
// INSIDE another async function. The emitter doesn't auto-chain async-to-
// async either, so the same dangling-symbol bug applies. Pre-fix, this
// produced a runtime crash via linker undefined-reference; now the
// checker rejects at compile time.
async void inner() { yield; }

async void outer() {
    inner();  // ← must be rejected even from inside another async fn
    yield;
}

void main() { }
